Guangdong Province Curbs Inflation
GUANGZHOU , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- South China 's Guangdong Province witnessed falling prices in January when compared with the previous year 's period .
Falling prices were recorded despite the fact that price hikes normally accompany the period between New Year 's and Spring Festival .
The retail price index for the prosperous province dropped by 1.7 percent on a year-on-year basis , with the consumer goods index falling by 0.4 percent .
Nonetheless , the two indices rose by 0.2 percent and 0.5 percent respectively when compared to December levels .
January prices for aquatics products and fresh fruit climbed , with falling prices for meat , poultry and eggs .
Prices for the major portion of 13 major daily necessities dropped , and the index for farming materials fell by 6.5 percent .
On the other hand , prices for service items jumped by 9.4 percent .
